    "Management": {
      "text": "Treat\nshock\nTreat underlying infection\nNecrotic tissue may require debridement\nCoagulopathy\ncorrection, in some cases\nTypically only if bleeding or need for procedure\nException:\nFFP\nusually indicated for neonatal purpura fulminans\nCryoprecipitate\n: consider if fibrinogen <100\nPlatelets\n: consider repletion if <50K with bleeding or <20K without bleeding\nFFP\n: consider repletion to goal of PT and PTT < 1.5 times the normal limit\nVitamin K\n,\nfolate",
